2	## 2. The Problem: Limitations of ESLint + Prettier\nThe current standard stack presents several bottlenecks in modern, large-scale Next.js environments:\n*   **Performance Latency:** ESLint (Node.js-based) is significantly slower, with linting times for medium-to-large codebases often exceeding 28 seconds.\n*   **"Configuration Hell":** Managing multiple configuration files (e.g., `.eslintrc`, `.prettierrc`) and resolving conflicts between 10–50+ dev dependencies creates substantial maintenance overhead.\n*   **CI/CD Drag:** Heavy linting processes increase total build time and operational costs.	[-0.0048366655,0.021416763,0.0004835987,-0.014253463,-0.014372993,-0.010475939,-0.05392002,-0.014894115,0.033034876,-0.05484865,-0.02064052,0.0154463425,-0.004648708,-0.016042067,-0.00844722,0.051833272,0.03883285,-0.017249059,-0.05084088,0.017638192,-0.025152348,-0.03062238,0.031397574,0.005772734,0.025000945,0.022310352,0.018290116,0.002757148,-0.04698197,0.16941775,-0.025067616,-0.008440068,0.027427863,-0.044224292,0.0036039965,-0.040977757,0.011046418,-0.000377569,-0.017110351,0.0059115677,0.010177497,0.014634784,-0.018698355,0.0040921294,-0.0088390345,0.0016698266,-0.018546073,-0.008465375,-0.014044161,-0.03042408,0.010219454,-0.0059854514,0.00053402124,-0.0068036066,0.008332049,0.0015359671,0.019615436,-0.011501802,0.02994627,-0.0044650855,-0.0071431026,-0.0013285633,0.046422154,0.037127234,0.0031834873,0.010567626,0.015011698,-0.025441732,0.021763835,0.019789739,0.013062317,0.029058862,-0.05221815,-0.00861682,0.012040816,-0.02333106,-0.04236471,0.03804164,-0.0014231793,0.02268487,-0.0036022624,-0.02294214,-0.049967613,-0.0057956395,0.02325955,0.03684246,0.020376049,0.010630237,-0.001085894,0.007885451,0.03797147,-0.014704648,0.021119997,-0.014152918,-0.030756963,0.030701777,-0.028763654,-0.008947469,-0.010175413,0.004974849,-0.025593119,-0.017257307,-0.012028493,0.011044487,-0.0031709995,0.03651683,0.00069515157,-0.034564693,0.018614106,-0.020656886,-0.05244199,-0